---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import screenshotModules from '../../assets/screenshots/landing-modules.png';
---

<section class="px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 md:py-24">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-12 md:mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        One platform, organized around your events.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        RaceNode is built around the way racing teams actually work: event by event. Each race weekend has its own workspace with its staff, cars, logistics, and meals. You prepare one event at a time â€” your tools should work the same way.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Screenshot -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl shadow-green-500/10">
      <Image
        src={screenshotModules}
        alt="RaceNode - Choose your module: Personal, Staff, Fleet, Racecars, Events, Management, Logistics"
        class="w-full h-auto"
        quality={85}
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
